# Copy to a local env file your shell loads, or export before running scripts.
# Files named *.env are gitignored by this repo — never commit real secrets.

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Adobe Illustrator (Beta) MCP — private connection values.
# See docs/illustrator-claw-public-setup.md and docs/adobe-illustrator-mcp-tools.md.
# Keep real URLs, tokens, and local paths in your private secret store; this
# file only documents the variable names.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Local Illustrator MCP server endpoint (do not commit real hostnames/ports).
# ILLUSTRATOR_MCP_URL=http://127.0.0.1:PORT

# Bearer token printed by Illustrator (Beta) when the MCP server is enabled.
# ILLUSTRATOR_MCP_BEARER_TOKEN=

# Optional: full local connection command if your AI tool needs one string.
# ILLUSTRATOR_MCP_CONNECTION=

# Adobe IMS / Creative Cloud OAuth credentials, if your tool integrates beyond
# the local MCP server (e.g. Firefly Services / Creative Cloud APIs).
# ADOBE_CLIENT_ID=
# ADOBE_CLIENT_SECRET=
# ADOBE_ORG_ID=
# ADOBE_TECHNICAL_ACCOUNT_ID=
# ADOBE_IMS_BASE_URL=https://ims-na1.adobelogin.com

# Local workspace + export paths used by Illustrator Claw / Codex agents.
# Keep these out of git so private project paths never leak.
# ILLUSTRATOR_WORKSPACE_PATH=
# ILLUSTRATOR_EXPORT_DIR=

# Model provider key used by your private Illustrator Claw / Codex agent runner.
# AI_MODEL_PROVIDER_API_KEY=

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional: tools/ollama-vision (local multimodal chat via Ollama).
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:11434
# OLLAMA_HOST=http://127.0.0.1:11434
# OLLAMA_MODEL=llava
# Qwen / Gemma vision presets (see workflows/ollama-qwen-gemma-vision.md):
# OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen2.5vl:7b
# OLLAMA_MODEL=qwen2.5vl:3b
# OLLAMA_MODEL=gemma3:4b
# OLLAMA_MODEL=gemma3:12b
